          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-17231 doc: Create script to generate man pages",
        "message": "LU-17231 doc: Create script to generate man pages\n\nCreated generate-param.sh script that can be used to generate\nthe bare bones of a man pages with the appropriate sections included.\n\nIn particular this script will be used to create pages for the new\nlustre parameter man pages, which there are several hundred.\n\nThis script can be used as follows:\n  generate-manpage.sh NAME SECTION [OUTPUT_FILE]\nor\n  generate-manpage.sh [DIR/]NAME.(1-8)\n\nfor example:\n  generate-manpage.sh lctl-list_param 8\nwill generate a single man page for the command 'lctl list_param'\nunder the folder Documentation/man8.\n\nor\n\n  generate-manpage.sh lctl-list_param 8 lustre/doc/lctl-list_param.8\nwill generate the man page in lustre/doc/lctl-list_param.8 instead\nof the default directory.\n\nor\n\n  generate-manpage.sh lctl-list_param.8\nwill generate the man page in lctl-list_param.8 in the current\ndirectory.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Frederick Dilger <fdilger@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I9b3ec2bf82aa947038aa9c1fb681f6573becec9d\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/60047\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Arshad Hussain <arshad.hussain@aeoncomputing.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Alex Deiter <adeiter@ddn.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
